The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	 Former Davis Cup coach Akhtar Ali has been shortlisted for the Mother Teresa Millennium Award for 2007 for his contribution to the sport. Sonia Gandhi is likely to hand over the award to him at a function in the city on Saturday.                 
	 AMCA-1 beat Luna CCC by eight wickets in the Swaran Malhotra cricket tournament on Sunday.       
	SUMMARISED SCORES      
	n Luna CCC 96/9 (Bijoy Chauhan 26; Pabak Dey 3/10). AMCA-1 98/2 (Vibek Keshari 37 n.o.). AMCA-1 won by 8 wkts.       
	nNorthern Park CCC 128/5 (Amit Tiwari 38; Avik Sarkar 36). Nabagram Sebak Sangha 132/2 (Kaushik Ghosh 65 n.o). Nabagram won by 8 wts.       
	nSouth Star CA 163/2 (Rithik Dey 44). CCD 109/7. South Star CA won by 54 runs.                                                                                                                                                                     
